<concept id="restorelostfocus" xml:lang="en-US">
   <title id="title__Toc50995551">RESTORELOSTFOCUS System Variable</title>
   <conbody>
      <section><title>Restore lost focus (Linux)</title><p>Specifies whether to restore a lost focus. Depending on window manager, focus may be lost by using short-lived windows like quad, tipsto. </p><p><table id="table_r32_ncz_hnb">
               <tgroup cols="2">
                  <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" />
                  <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="3*" />
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/type" />
                        <entry><p conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/boolean" /></entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/saved_in" />
                        <entry><p conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/registry" /></entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry conkeyref="system_variable_warehouse/possible_values" />
                        <entry>
                           <p>Off (0): Do not try to recover from focus loss.</p>
                           <p>On (1): Attempt automatic recovery from focus loss.</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table></p></section>
   </conbody>
</concept>
